        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): make control-plane write rate limit configurable",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe control-plane write rate limit (`config.apply`, `config.patch`, `update.run`) is currently hardcoded at 3 requests per 60-second window per device+IP bucket. This is too low for multi-tenant deployments where automated config sync routinely pushes many RPCs during auth delivery, model config, and workspace push cycles.\n\nThis PR makes both `maxRequests` and `windowMs` configurable via the gateway config file under `gateway.controlPlane.rateLimit`, following the same pattern as the existing `gateway.auth.rateLimit` configuration.\n\n**Config example** (`openclaw.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"gateway\": {\n    \"controlPlane\": {\n      \"rateLimit\": {\n        \"maxRequests\": 30,\n        \"windowMs\": 60000\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/config/types.gateway.ts`**: New `GatewayControlPlaneRateLimitConfig` type + `controlPlane` field on `GatewayConfig`\n- **`src/gateway/control-plane-rate-limit.ts`**: Replace hardcoded constants with configurable values via `configureControlPlaneRateLimit()`\n- **`src/gateway/server-methods.ts`**: Dynamic limit string in rate limit error details (was hardcoded `\"3 per 60s\"`)\n- **`src/gateway/server.impl.ts`**: Wire config reading at gateway startup\n- **Tests**: 3 new test cases — custom `maxRequests`, custom `windowMs`, and dynamic error details\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- Follows the `gateway.auth.rateLimit` pattern exactly\n- Backward compatible: defaults unchanged at 3 req/60s\n- `consumeControlPlaneWriteBudget` return type extended with `maxRequests` and `windowMs` for dynamic error strings\n- `configureControlPlaneRateLimit()` clears existing buckets so config changes take effect immediately\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Existing 4 rate limit tests pass (default behavior unchanged)\n- [x] New test: custom `maxRequests` allows more requests before blocking\n- [x] New test: custom `windowMs` produces shorter retry windows\n- [x] New test: error details reflect configured limit, not hardcoded default",
